4.11	Llamasoft	Jeff Minter	Jeff 'Yak' Minter (born in Reading, 22 April 1962 ) is a British video game designer and programmer. He is the founder of software house Llamasoft and his recent works include Neon (2004), a non-game music visualization program that has been built into the Xbox 360 console, and the video games Space Giraffe (Xbox Live Arcade, 2007 and PC, 2008), and Space Invaders Extreme (Xbox Live Arcade, May 2009).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Jeff_Minter_-_GDC_2007.jpg/200px-Jeff_Minter_-_GDC_2007.jpg
